    <div class="text text-4">

      <p>
<strong style="margin-top:30px">#31DaysOfHappy Events :</strong> Join us for the launch of our event on <strong>Friday, May 1</strong> at 12pm on the lower level of Edmonton City Centre near the LRT entrance. This event promises to be tons of fun and happy times with a fashion show, a DJ, choreographed dances, “Snap-Happy” photo opportunities, happy-face nail art from Spasation, a DAVIDs TEA tea break, and happy-face cupcakes from The Art of Cake! Our community partner, The Support Network, will also be there to provide information and answer any questions you may have. Then, continue to join us for each Thursday in May from 12-1pm in the same location of Edmonton City Centre. There will be “Snap-Happy” photo opportunities, as well as information from The Support Network at each of the following events:</p>

      <p><strong>Thursday, May 7</strong> : <i>“Happy Hugs”</i> with the Coca-Cola ‘Hug-Me’ machine. You don’t want to miss this opportunity to hug the machine and get free product!</p>
      <p><strong>Thursday, May 14</strong> : <i>“Happy Appy”</i> with DAVIDs TEA and The Art of Cake giving away delicious treats during the lunch hour.</p>
      <p><strong>Thursday, May 21</strong> : <i>“Happy Nails”</i> with Spasation, doing happy-face nail art for everyone who is interested. Gentleman, that means you, too!</p>
      <p><strong>Thursday, May 28</strong> : <i>“Happy Meals”</i> with L’Azia – get there early as there’s limited supply!</p><br>
</div>
    <div class="element element-3"></div>
 
      <p>
<strong>Community Partner :</strong> Our Community Partner for #31DaysofHappy is 
<a href="//www.thesupportnetwork.com/" target="_blank">The Support Network</a>
The Support Network is the umbrella organization that overlooks the operations of the Crisis Support Centre, 211 Alberta - Edmonton and Area, and Wellness Network. The Support Network envisions a healthy community where people transition from feeling helpless and isolated to feeling hopeful and engaged. This month will be the 40th anniversary of the Crisis Support Centre’s Edmonton Distress Line. This 24/7 phone line is available to those in distress, as well as suicide awareness programs, and online crisis services; the Centre is available to everyone who needs it, whenever crisis strikes. If you or someone you know is in distress, call 482-HELP (4357) or take the opportunity to visit The Support Network’s booth at any of our events in May on the Lower Level of Edmonton City Centre.
</p>
